<div id="review_1291139367" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1291139367" />
    <a title="Jeff Powers" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/28415586-jeff-powers"><img alt="Jeff Powers" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1457316378p2/28415586.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1291139367?book_show_action=true">Jul 01, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jeff Powers" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jeff Powers" href="/user/show/28415586-jeff-powers">Jeff Powers</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/28415586-jeff-powers?shelf=diversity-in-fiction-challenge">diversity-in-fiction-challenge</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1291139367" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1887132674318563431">It took me ages to finally track down a copy of this book, and I am now excited that I have slowly been finding others. Hambly has always been a skilled fantasy writer in my books, but it was this long running series that really interested me. Living amongst New Orleans and its complex history for a time, along with my love of mysteries, historical fiction, and books featuring a protagonist other than the accepted white or heteronormative hero, all made me crave this story. And I was not disappo</span>
  <span id="freeText1887132674318563431" style="display:none">It took me ages to finally track down a copy of this book, and I am now excited that I have slowly been finding others. Hambly has always been a skilled fantasy writer in my books, but it was this long running series that really interested me. Living amongst New Orleans and its complex history for a time, along with my love of mysteries, historical fiction, and books featuring a protagonist other than the accepted white or heteronormative hero, all made me crave this story. And I was not disappointed. Hambly offers a unique and personal viewpoint of a lesser known part of history and weaves an intriguing tale of murder, but also historical context and culture that few writers can deliver well. Her efforts of research are very present. I was worried going into this as to how well a white woman could depict the experiences of a Black man in the south just after the Louisiana Purchase, but with help from Octavia Butler as a content reader, she really knocked it out of the park. I cant wait to find more of these, I hope more people get a chance to check them out as well. A wonderful glimpse at history and character in the deep south. Well recommended.</span>
  <a data-text-id="1887132674318563431" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


