<div id="review_98902763" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/98902763" />
    <a title="Lorena" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/251417-lorena"><img alt="Lorena" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1489184320p2/251417.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/98902763?book_show_action=true">Jul 11, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Lorena" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Lorena" href="/user/show/251417-lorena">Lorena</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780553102581" href="/book/show/1064015.A_Free_Man_of_Color">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/251417-lorena?shelf=historical-fiction">historical-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/251417-lorena?shelf=mystery">mystery</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/251417-lorena?shelf=lgbtqia">lgbtqia</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/251417-lorena?shelf=black-author-characters">black-author-characters</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer98902763" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15162400534951747319">Don&apos;t know who wrote the Goodreads description for this book, but it&apos;s bizarre and largely incorrect. This is a terrific book, which reminded me somewhat of the flavor of Kindred, by Octavia Butler, with the exception of the fact that Benjamin January is very much a man of his place and time - the son of a black slave and a mulatto (half black, half white) slave, freed when his mother was purchased (and then freed) to be a Creole man&apos;s mistress in New Orleans. The mystery is well done and takes </span>
  <span id="freeText15162400534951747319" style="display:none">Don't know who wrote the Goodreads description for this book, but it's bizarre and largely incorrect. This is a terrific book, which reminded me somewhat of the flavor of Kindred, by Octavia Butler, with the exception of the fact that Benjamin January is very much a man of his place and time - the son of a black slave and a mulatto (half black, half white) slave, freed when his mother was purchased (and then freed) to be a Creole man's mistress in New Orleans. The mystery is well done and takes some interesting turns, but the best part of the book is the atmosphere and the terrific detail about the infinite stratification and intricate workings of New Orleans society in the years after the Louisiana Purchase but before the Civil War. </span>
  <a data-text-id="15162400534951747319" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


